PROJECT CONTEXT
 
Laravel12, Livewire 3 and Flux 2.21 are already installed. We have a custom Laravel package located in:
 
packages/IctInterface
Change name and rename IctInterface folder to zoe; namespaces and all references too. 
 
This package provides a dynamic interface system that allows:
- Creation and configuration of Reports (record lists)
- Dynamic column management per report
- Dynamic form management (insert/edit)
- Filter forms
- Modal forms
- Dynamic form fields
- Multiselect functionality
- CSV/XLSX export
- User management
- User profiles
- upload files
- creation and configurazione main menu (container of reports)
- creation and configuration of Options
 
The current implementation is based on:
- Laravel (older version)
- Bootstrap
- jQuery
 
GOAL
 
Refactor and upgrade the entire package to:
 
- Laravel 12
- Livewire 3
- Bootstrap 5
- Flux 2.12 (UI layer)
- if possibile replace fontawesome with icons livewire (if available), otherwise upgrade fontawesome to latest version
- Replace jQuery with Livewire/Flux login for ajax calls and dynamic functionalities on the pages.
 
IMPORTANT CONSTRAINTS

1. Database structure (tables and migrations) MUST remain unchanged.
2. All existing functionalities must be preserved.
3. The package must remain reusable as a Laravel package.
4. Remove jQuery completely and replace all jQuery logic with Laravel/Flux logic.
5. Maintain frontend logic and replace where necessary with Livewire and Flux Logix
6. All forms and reports funcionally have to implements with livewire/flux logic, no jQuery.
7. Remove package formBuilder and replace it with livewire/Flux logic
8. Maintain, where possible, bootstrap logic upgraded to version 5 for general layout (headers, containers, cards, etc.)
9. Actual logic provides the requst variable "report" (report_id). This is mandatory on every links less dashboard
10. Maintain all routes on routes/web.php

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS TO PRESERVE

1. Report management:
   - Create, edit, delete reports
   - Configure columns per report
   - Sorting
   - Filtering
   - Pagination
 
2. Column management:
   - Dynamic columns
   - Visibility toggle
   - Ordering
   - preserve type data (text, number, enum, date, etc.)
 
3. Forms:
   - Insert/Edit forms
   - Filter forms
   - Modal forms
   - Dynamic form fields
   - Validation
 
4. Field types:
   - text
   - textarea
   - select
   - multiselect
   - date
   - checkbox
   - etc.
 
5. Multiselect:
   - Must work with Livewire
   - No jQuery-based plugins
   - Support for relationships
   - Remove javascript logic
 
6. Export:
   - CSV export
   - XLSX export
   - Keep backend export logic
   - Refactor frontend triggers to Livewire actions

7. Users and profiles:
   - Use livewire user management (login, register, change pass)
   - table reference must be users
   - middlware authentication must have the same logic of AuthIct
      - report variable must be mandatory less on dashboard
      - the same session variable must be available (loggedUser, is_admin, roles, profiles, etc.)
   - Maintain profile association with current login linked to table users
   - Refactor UI to Livewire + Bootstrap

8. Main layout
    - maintain header on all pages (login included) with app name on the left and user name and link logout on the right
    - the main color (green, red, blue, etc) must be customizable on custom style.css or .env variable
    - maintain navigation accordation menu on the left, where the content element are records of menu table and submenu elemnt are record of report table
    - highlight color must be the same of header color

9. migrations
    - Get and copy in pachages/zoe/Database/Migrations folder migrations files refer to package tables (report. report_columns, forms, etc.) in database/migration folder in the root. Exclude vw_users view file.

10. Date range
    - Use Livewire date range component
    - Refactor UI to Livewire + Bootstrap

TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS
 
- Use modern Laravel 12 conventions ONLY on new files
- Improve existing code readability and maintainability
- Use typed properties and return types
- Remove obsolete helpers
- Maintain all poackages helpers
- Follow SOLID principles
- Avoid duplicated logic
- Use service classes where appropriate